parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Takata Airbag Recall - Unavailable Parts and Delayed Repair
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure to replace the Takata airbag can cause serious injury or death in the event of an accident, as the airbag may deploy with excessive force or rupture, sending shrapnel into the passenger compartment.
symptoms: as the issue is related to a potential future failure.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Ignition coil failure can cause the engine to stall or fail to start, leading to safety risks and inconvenience.
Electrical system failure can cause various safety risks, including airbag failure, battery drain, and fire hazards.
Keyless ignition system failure can cause the vehicle to roll or move without the driver's intention, leading to accidents and injuries.
symptoms: Vehicle rolling or moving without driver's intention
failure to shift into park gear.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: SCM failure can cause the vehicle to become inoperable, leading to safety risks and inconvenience.
Wire insulation failure can cause electrical short circuits, leading to safety risks and fire hazards.
The failure of the electronic parking brake module can cause the parking brake light to illuminate randomly or constantly, which can lead to confusion and potentially cause accidents.
symptoms: The parking brake light is on
the parking brake module is faulty
the parking brake switch is faulty.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The design of the brake pedal can cause the car to accelerate unexpectedly when the brake pedal is slowly depressed, leading to accidents or near-misses.
symptoms: The car accelerates unexpectedly when the brake pedal is depressed
the brake pedal can be depressed to the floor with little pressure
the harder the brake pedal is pressed
